You are in your bedroom.  You looked at the clock. It's 3:14 in the morning and you are awake... And it's the night before your birthday.  Then, you notice that everything is a little scrambled and out of place.  You jump out of the bed but surprisingly you remain floating in the air.  After a little while, you touch the ground and  looking carefully to everything, you realize it's a dream. There's no way out and you need to wake up.

 Along the north wall, there is a bed, where you use to sleep. A closed box is in a corner; the label says "Toys". A small chair is floating in the air. You better grab it! There is a mat covering the whole floor. Against the east wall there is an old, small desk.

You can see the bed, the box, the chair, the floor mat, the desk and the clock.
> about

> about
A short fun game to you, in IFCOMP 2-0-1-3

Commands to use are LOOK,TAKE, CUT, OPEN, MIX...WITH..., BURN and BREAK.

Things in your room must be remade. Experiment!

If you are clueless, the last resort is type WALKTHROUGH.

For those who helped with the game, the right command to type is CREDITS.

